        <title>Accelerating Truck</title>
		<statement>
			<p>
				
			</p>
		    <p>A truck is traveling in a straight line on level ground, and is accelerating uniformly. Two ropes are tied to the back of the truck. The other end of each rope is tied to a bucket: the bucket tied to rope 1 has a larger mass than the bucket tied to rope 2. You notice that each rope is hanging from the back of the truck at a fixed (but potentially different) angle. Is the angle of rope 1 <em>greater than</em>, <em>less than</em>, or <em>equal to</em> the angle of rope 2?</p>
