	<project xml:id="pa_for-02">
        <title>The Water Slide</title>
		<statement>
			<p>
				
			</p>
		    <p>You go down a water slide of length <m>L</m> that makes an angle <m>\theta</m> with the horizontal, 
			starting from rest. Do not neglect friction (use <m>\mu_k</m> as the coefficient of kinetic friction). 
			Determine your acceleration.</p>
		</statement>
		<hint>
		    <p>To make sense of your answer, use special-case analysis in the case that friction can be neglected.</p>
		</hint>
	</project>

